# 002 -- Renderer-host adapters (ChartHosts.fs) + chart panel

> **Ordering note.** This slice carries Part **U5** of the parent spec. The
> spec numbers U5 after U3/U4, but U5.1 delivers `ChartHosts.fs` — the shared
> renderer-host seam that U3/U4/U6/U7/U8 **MUST reuse** rather than embed their
> own hosting. Because the arc-runner implements slices in manifest order, this
> shared seam must land before its consumers, so U5 is sequenced second (right
> after the U1 foundation). Only U1 is required by the spec to land first; the
> remaining parts may be ordered to satisfy their dependency graph.

## Spec reference

- `C:\GitHub\Berreman\specs\0024\.spec-md` -- parent spec this slice belongs to (Part U5).
- Ancestor: spec 0022 (delivered the tested Avalonia-free MVU core; clone-swap deferred, §A.9 / AC-A8).
- Operator-plan source: `specs/0022/.manual/018-ui-wiring-plan.md` (superseded; codebase wins on conflicts).

## Inherited from parent spec

### Binding constraints (from `.spec-md` ## 0)

These apply to every part of this arc, including this slice.

- **0.1 — Freeze the tested core.** The implementation MUST NOT edit any
  model / `update` / projection / persistence module under
  `OpticalConstructor.Domain`, `OpticalConstructor.Storage`,
  `OpticalConstructor.Optimization`, or the Avalonia-free logic modules in
  `OpticalConstructor.Ui` (e.g. `ConstructionPage.fs`, `StackEditor.fs`,
  `Workspace.fs`, `SynthesisFitPage.fs`, `JobRunner.fs`, `Schematic.fs`,
  `SystemView3D.fs`, `UserEnvironment.fs`, the `Charts/` and `Sources/`
  builders). These modules are Avalonia-free by mandate and carry the existing
  passing suite. New view code MUST live in **new sibling `*View.fs` modules**
  and the composition root. Adding a `Compile Include` line for a new file to
  `OpticalConstructor.Ui.fsproj` is permitted and is not an edit to a frozen
  module.

- **0.2 — Public FuncUI NuGet only; no clone reference.** All view code MUST be
  authored against the public MIT `Avalonia.FuncUI` 1.6.0 DSL surface already
  referenced by both projects. The implementation MUST NOT add a
  `PackageReference` or `ProjectReference` to
  `C:/GitHub/Avalonia.FuncUI.Clone/`, and MUST NOT depend on any clone-specific
  API. The clone-swap decision (spec 0022 §A.9 / AC-A8) stays deferred; this arc
  does not touch it.

- **0.3 — Public-Avalonia layout primitives only for docking.** Panel
  layout/visibility/dock MUST be rendered with public Avalonia
  `DockPanel` / `Grid` / `GridSplitter`. The richer drag-to-redock / floating
  chrome is the deferred clone's responsibility and MUST NOT be invented here.

- **0.4 — UI-thread marshaling for every off-thread dispatch.** Any `dispatch`
  invoked from a background callback (a `JobRunner` progress or completion
  callback, a file-IO continuation) MUST be marshaled onto the UI thread via
  `Avalonia.Threading.Dispatcher.UIThread.Post`. A direct cross-thread
  `dispatch` is a defect. Every effectful `Cmd` this spec introduces MUST honour
  this rule.

- **0.5 — Non-serializable handles live outside the model.** The root MVU model
  MUST remain pure and serializable. `CancellationTokenSource`, live renderer
  control instances (`AvaPlot`, `WebView2`), and the Avalonia
  `IStorageProvider` MUST be held in the view/host layer (a component
  `ctx.useState` or a host field), never as fields of the root model.

- **0.6 — Persistence facts (no new committable file types).** Committable
  project files are written as `<projectName>.ocproj.json` under the project's
  working folder by `ConstructionPage.saveProject`
  (`Berreman/OpticalConstructor/OpticalConstructor.Ui/ConstructionPage.fs:229`,
  path built at `ConstructionPage.fs:225`). Derived `.binz` sidecars are written
  under a per-project `.sidecars/` subfolder via the single shared seam
  `Storage.Sidecar.derivedArtefactPath`
  (`Berreman/OpticalConstructor/OpticalConstructor.Storage/Sidecar.fs:36`,
  directory at `Sidecar.fs:30`). `*.binz` and `*.autosave` are already ignored
  in the repository root `.gitignore` (`.gitignore:336`, `.gitignore:340`) and
  `.sidecars/` carries no committable state, so this arc introduces **no new
  committable file type** and triggers no `.gitignore` override work. The
  per-user environment-settings file is user-local, not committed.

- **0.7 — Gate roster.** This arc adds two new gates,
  `.gates/OpticalConstructor/ui-smoke.gates` (new) and
  `.gates/OpticalConstructor/ui-tests.gates` (new), modelled on the existing
  command-gate format (`.gates/OpticalConstructor/constructor-unit-tests.gates`,
  `.gates/Berreman/build.gates`). Every slice in this arc MUST end
  `build`-green, `constructor-unit-tests`-green, `ui-smoke`-green, and (once the
  UI test project exists) `ui-tests`-green.

### Acceptance criteria owned by this slice

- **AC-U5.1:** After a sweep, the `chart` panel MUST render the `Plot1DView` result
  in an `AvaPlot` and `Refresh()` on subsequent model changes.
- **AC-U5.2:** After editing chart settings, the applied axis/scale/legend changes
  MUST reach the plot via `applyToScottPlot`/`applyToPlotly` (not a re-applied
  copy), and cursor placement MUST update `Readout.Markers`.

### Files in scope owned by this slice

- `Berreman/OpticalConstructor/OpticalConstructor.Ui/ChartHosts.fs` (new) — AvaPlot / WebView2 / Canvas renderer-host adapters.
- `Berreman/OpticalConstructor/OpticalConstructor.Ui/ChartView.fs` (new) — chart panel view.

### File:line references owned by this slice

- `Plot1DView.renderSweep` (`Berreman/OpticalConstructor/OpticalConstructor.Ui/Charts/Plot1DView.fs:55`), `renderComparison` (`Plot1DView.fs:62`), `renderFieldDepth` (`Plot1DView.fs:68`), `renderDispersion` (`Plot1DView.fs:74`) — all return `ScottPlot.Plot`.
- `ChartSettings.ChartSettings` (`Charts/ChartSettings.fs:50`); `ChartSettings.applyToScottPlot` (`Charts/ChartSettings.fs:138`); `applyToPlotly` (`Charts/ChartSettings.fs:179`).
- `Readout.Markers` (`Charts/Readout.fs:15`).
- `Plot3DView.render` (`Charts/Plot3DView.fs:29`, returns `Plotly.NET.GenericChart`).

## Scope

This slice delivers the shared renderer-host adapters every other panel reuses,
plus the chart panel itself — the primary results surface. It adds `ChartHosts.fs`
(an `AvaPlot` host for `ScottPlot.Plot`, a `WebView2` host for
`Plotly.NET.GenericChart`, and a `Canvas` host for 2-D geometry), then renders the
1-D charts in the `AvaPlot` host, the 3-D surface in the `WebView2` host, and
wires chart-settings controls and on-plot cursor readouts. It adds the `Chart`
`RootMsg` case to the `Shell.fs` surface authored in slice 001.

## Requirements

### R-1. U5.1 — Renderer-host adapters (the reusable seam)

The implementation MUST add a new module
`OpticalConstructor.Ui/ChartHosts.fs` (new) with three small adapter views,
authored against the public FuncUI DSL: (a) an `AvaPlot` host for a
`ScottPlot.Plot`, (b) a `WebView2` host for a `Plotly.NET.GenericChart`
(`GenericChart.toEmbeddedHTML` → `NavigateToString`; Windows-only is acceptable —
the app targets win-x64), and (c) a `Canvas` host for 2-D geometry (used by
U6/U8). Each adapter MUST host its control via `ContentControl.create`
(or `View.createWithOutlet` to retain a handle for `Refresh()`), and MUST honour
§0.5 (the control instance lives in the host layer) and §U1.8 (graceful
"unavailable" placeholder when the runtime is absent). U3/U4/U6/U8 MUST reuse
these adapters rather than embed their own hosting.

### R-2. U5.2 — 1-D charts

The `chart` panel view MUST render `Plot1DView.renderSweep`
(`Berreman/OpticalConstructor/OpticalConstructor.Ui/Charts/Plot1DView.fs:55`),
`renderComparison` (`Plot1DView.fs:62`), `renderFieldDepth` (`Plot1DView.fs:68`),
and `renderDispersion` (`Plot1DView.fs:74`) — all return `ScottPlot.Plot` — in
the U5.1 `AvaPlot` host, calling `Refresh()` on model change.

### R-3. U5.3 — Chart settings and cursor readouts

Chart-settings controls MUST edit `ChartSettings.ChartSettings`
(`Charts/ChartSettings.fs:50`) and dispatch `Chart …`; the applied settings MUST
reach the plot through the existing `ChartSettings.applyToScottPlot`
(`Charts/ChartSettings.fs:138`) / `applyToPlotly` (`Charts/ChartSettings.fs:179`)
seams (the chart builders already call these — the view MUST NOT re-apply axis
styling itself). On-plot cursors MUST edit `Readout.Markers`
(`Charts/Readout.fs:15`) held in the model and dispatch `Chart …`.

### R-4. U5.4 — 3-D surface chart

The 3-D surface (`Plot3DView.render`, `Charts/Plot3DView.fs:29`, returns
`Plotly.NET.GenericChart`) MUST be hosted in the U5.1 WebView2 adapter.

## Non-requirements

- Does NOT render the materials, sources, results, or fit panels (U3/U4/U6/U7).
- Does NOT recompute any chart geometry or re-apply axis styling the builders
  already apply via `applyToScottPlot`/`applyToPlotly`.
- Does NOT add a second hosting implementation; U3/U4/U6/U8 reuse `ChartHosts.fs`.
- Does NOT edit any frozen core module (§0.1); the chart builders under `Charts/`
  are frozen and only called, not modified.

