## Testing plan

Gates that apply to this slice (run in order; first failure short-circuits):
`build`, `unit-tests`, `constructor-unit-tests`, `impl-log-structure`,
`state-of-world-structure`, `ui-smoke`, `ui-tests`.

- `ui-smoke`: the `chart` panel renders one frame headlessly; the WebView2 /
  AvaPlot / Canvas adapters degrade to an "unavailable" placeholder rather than
  throwing when the native runtime is absent (§U1.8).
- `ui-tests`: a chart-panel headless view test asserts the chart controls mount
  over a known `RootModel`, a settings edit dispatches `Chart …`, and cursor
  placement updates `Readout.Markers` (AC-U5.1 / AC-U5.2).
- `build`, `constructor-unit-tests`, `unit-tests`: green; no frozen module edits.

## Risks

- **Medium: native renderer hosting under headless.** The `WebView2` host and the
  `AvaPlot` host wrap native controls that cannot initialise on the headless
  platform or on a machine without the WebView2 Evergreen runtime. The adapters
  MUST render a graceful "unavailable" placeholder (§U1.8 / §0.5) so the
  `ui-smoke` gate renders a frame for the `chart` panel without throwing. Getting
  the `View.createWithOutlet` / `Refresh()` handle retention right while keeping
  the control instance in the host layer (not the model, §0.5) is the main worry.

## Hand-off

- `ChartHosts.fs` is now the single renderer-host seam. Slices 004 (materials),
  005 (sources), 006 (results), 007 (fit), and 008 (lifecycle/3-D) reuse the
  `AvaPlot` / `WebView2` / `Canvas` adapters from this slice and MUST NOT embed
  their own hosting.
- The `Chart` `RootMsg` case is now wired in `Shell.fs`.
- Emit the state-of-the-world `gates:` YAML block with this round's baseline
  counts so the next slice's `count_at_least` gates have a baseline.
